# Copy to .env and fill in. Never commit the real .env.
# The LLM is provider-agnostic (LiteLLM). Portfolio/MF analysis works with NO LLM at all;
# only the written research notes need one. Pick ONE option below.

# --- Option A: NVIDIA NIM (free hosted open models, US cloud) ---
# 1) Make a free NVIDIA developer account at build.nvidia.com
# 2) Open any model, click "Get API Key" (you get an nvapi-... key, no credit card)
# 3) Uncomment and set (confirm the exact model id on the model's build.nvidia.com page):
# LLM_MODEL=nvidia_nim/deepseek-ai/deepseek-v3.2
# NVIDIA_NIM_API_KEY=nvapi-xxxxxxxx

# --- Option B: Ollama (fully local, free, data never leaves your machine) ---
# 1) Install Ollama, then `ollama pull qwen2.5:7b`  (qwen2.5 is reliable at strict JSON)
# 2) Use the ollama_chat/ prefix (it sends the system prompt correctly):
# LLM_MODEL=ollama_chat/qwen2.5:7b
# LLM_API_BASE=http://localhost:11434
# (verified working end-to-end via scripts/live_smoke.py on 2026-06-18)

# --- Option C: any other LiteLLM-supported provider ---
# LLM_MODEL=<litellm model string, e.g. openrouter/... , deepseek/... , anthropic/...>
# LLM_API_KEY=...
# LLM_API_BASE=...   # optional, only if the provider needs a custom endpoint
